---
// Review.astro — Real 30-Day Daily-Use Test
const minorDays = [6, 13, 21, 27]; // days with small issues
const days = Array.from({ length: 30 }, (_, i) => ({
  day: i + 1,
  minor: minorDays.includes(i + 1),
}));

const pros = [
  "Smooth playback on 26 of 30 days",
  "Great picture quality, clean audio",
  "Easy to navigate with the remote",
  "Huge library — always something new",
];
const cons = [
  "Occasional buffering on one server",
  "A couple of minor UI hiccups",
  "Needs solid internet for true 4K",
];
---

<section id="review" class="bg-ink-2 py-20 sm:py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 sm:px-8">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-neon">Honest Review</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
      A real 30-day daily-use test
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-base leading-relaxed text-muted sm:text-lg">
      We used NetMirror TV every day for a month on a Firestick and an Android TV. Here's how it
      actually held up — no sugar-coating.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[260px_1fr] lg:items-start">
      <!-- rating card -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-line bg-ink p-6 text-center">
        <div class="text-5xl font-extrabold text-fg">8.4<span class="text-2xl text-muted">/10</span></div>
        <div class="mt-2 flex items-center justify-center gap-1 text-neon">
          {Array.from({ length: 5 }).map((_, i) => (
            <svg class={`h-5 w-5 ${i < 4 ? "fill-current" : "fill-line"}`} viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2l2.9 6.3 6.9.7-5.1 4.6 1.4 6.8L12 17.8 5.9 20.4l1.4-6.8L2.2 9l6.9-.7L12 2z"/></svg>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted">Verified daily-use score</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 30-day grid -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-line bg-ink p-6">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-fg">30-Day log</h3>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-xs text-muted">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-sm bg-neon-3"></span>Smooth</span>
            <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5"><span class="h-2.5 w-2.5 rounded-sm bg-amber-400"></span>Minor issue</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-10 gap-1.5">
          {days.map((d) => (
            <div
              title={`Day ${d.day}${d.minor ? " — minor issue" : " — smooth"}`}
              class={`flex aspect-square items-center justify-center rounded-[5px] text-[10px] font-semibold ${d.minor ? "bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-600" : "bg-neon-3/15 text-neon-3"}`}
            >
              {d.day}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-muted">
          <strong class="text-fg">26 days</strong> were completely smooth. The
          <strong class="text-fg"> 4 off-days</strong> were minor and cleared up after switching
          servers or a quick app restart.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- pros / cons -->
    <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-line bg-ink p-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2 text-base font-bold text-fg">
          <span class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-neon-3/15 text-neon-3">+</span>
          What we liked
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5">
          {pros.map((p) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm text-muted">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-neon-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
              {p}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-line bg-ink p-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-2 text-base font-bold text-fg">
          <span class="flex h-6 w-6 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-ink-3 text-muted">–</span>
          Could be better
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2.5">
          {cons.map((c) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-sm text-muted">
              <svg class="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
              {c}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-8 rounded-2xl border border-line bg-ink p-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-muted">
      <strong class="text-fg">Verdict:</strong> For a free app, NetMirror TV is genuinely good. The
      library is massive, playback is mostly flawless, and the remote experience feels native. If
      you watch on a TV and don't want five subscriptions, it's an easy recommend.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
